Package: BaRcodes
Title: Custom R tools for collection, tracking, and curation of biological samples using 1D or 2D barcodes
Version: 0.0.0.9100
Authors@R: person("Robert", "Colautti", email = "robert.colautti@queensu.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: baRcodes is a set of R commands for generating and printing barcodes.
    The ID codes can be generated in a hierachy or input from a list. IDs are 
    converted to 2-dimensional barcodes (QR Codes) for printing on sticker 
    sheets compatible with a standard laser printer
Depends: R (>= 3.4.2)
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    grDevices,
    grid,
    gridExtra,
    qrcode
Suggests: testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
